        <div id="slide-2" class="slide-container">
            <div class="slide-content">
                <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold">The Laws of Thought</h2>
                <p class="text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto mt-4">In his groundbreaking 1854 book, "An Investigation of the Laws of Thought," Boole introduced a new type of algebra. **Boolean algebra** represents logical statements with two values: **True (1)** and **False (0)**. His system used operators like **AND** ($x \cdot y$), **OR** ($x+y$), and **NOT** ($\bar{x}$).</p>
                <img src="https://placehold.co/400x300/e5e7eb/4b5563?text=Book%20Cover%20Placeholder" alt="Representation of Boolean algebra" class="mt-8 mx-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg">
